<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<CustomField xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <fullName>ApprovalStatus__c</fullName>
    <description>- Picklist values depend on the Approval Process status. 
Once Submitted for Approval, status will change from empty to &quot;Submitted&quot; and will be automatically updated according to the Approver answer (Rejected or Approved). 
- Sales can also Recall and status will be changed to Recalled.

- Approval Status value fields are used in the Validation Rule  &quot;Quote_approved_before_Quot_or_Order_Sent&quot; . So that the Quote Status can&apos;t be changed if the Quote is not approved. (if approval needed).

- Approval Status value fields is used  in the Lightning Component Quote page to have &quot;Approval Needed / on going / Approved &quot; banner. 
Also used to have the frame &quot;Reasons for Approval&quot;.</description>
    <externalId>false</externalId>
    <label>Approval Status</label>
    <required>false</required>
    <trackFeedHistory>false</trackFeedHistory>
    <trackHistory>false</trackHistory>
    <trackTrending>false</trackTrending>
    <type>Picklist</type>
    <valueSet>
        <restricted>true</restricted>
        <valueSetDefinition>
            <sorted>false</sorted>
            <value>
                <fullName>Pending</fullName>
                <color>#0B6FCE</color>
